Description:
  Pull content from the NorthCloud Search API and persist entities via registered mappers

Usage:
  northcloud:sync [options]

Options:
  -l, --limit=LIMIT              Maximum hits to fetch [default: "20"]
  -s, --since=SINCE              Fetch content from this date (YYYY-MM-DD)
      --dry-run                  Report what would be created without persisting
      --explain                  Show skip reason breakdown and sampled hit diagnostics
      --sample=SAMPLE            Capture up to N created/skipped samples in output [default: "10"]
      --report-json=REPORT-JSON  Write sync report JSON to this path
  -h, --help                     Display help for the given command. When no command is given display help for the list command
      --silent                   Do not output any message
  -q, --quiet                    Only errors are displayed. All other output is suppressed
  -V, --version                  Display this application version
      --ansi|--no-ansi           Force (or disable --no-ansi) ANSI output
  -n, --no-interaction           Do not ask any interactive question
  -v|vv|vvv, --verbose           Increase the verbosity of messages: 1 for normal output, 2 for more verbose output and 3 for debug
